      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>Chinese</strong> <strong>rice</strong> <strong>wine</strong>, <strong>chicken stock</strong>, <strong>double cream </strong>and <strong>wholegrain</strong> <strong>mustard</strong> with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>creamy mustard sauce</strong></p>",
